<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="210" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1402,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1402,1428]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">Remarks.</emphasis>
In the descriptions of 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint 1974" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[527,801,1402,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipenis">
<emphasis box="[527,544,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[559,675,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">brevipenis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S. Jr." box="[684,801,1402,1428]" firstAuthor="Flint" journalOrPublisher="Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 151" part="14" refId="ref15088" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (1974) The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 14, 1 - 151." title="The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV" type="journal article" year="1974">Flint 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Flint 1974" authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[859,1125,1402,1428]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fimbriata">
<emphasis box="[859,876,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[892,996,1402,1428]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">fimbriata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S. Jr." box="[1005,1125,1402,1428]" firstAuthor="Flint" journalOrPublisher="Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 151" part="14" refId="ref15088" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (1974) The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 14, 1 - 151." title="The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV" type="journal article" year="1974">Flint 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Flint, O. S. Jr." box="[1138,1274,1402,1428]" firstAuthor="Flint" journalOrPublisher="Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="1 - 151" part="14" refId="ref15088" refString="Flint, O. S. Jr. (1974) The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV. Studies on the Fauna of Suriname and other Guyanas, 14, 1 - 151." title="The Trichoptera of Surinam. Studies of Neotropical caddisflies, XV" type="journal article" year="1974">Flint (1974)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that these two species constituted a particular group within the genus, differing in several aspects from the other species known until that time. Here, together with another 3 species (
<taxonomicName authority="Olah &amp; Johanson 2011" authorityName="Olah &amp; Johanson" authorityYear="2011" box="[860,1303,1474,1500]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="buborektala">
<emphasis box="[860,877,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[893,1027,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">buborektala</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Olah, J. &amp; Johanson, K. A." box="[1037,1303,1474,1500]" firstAuthor="Olah" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="117 - 255" part="103" refId="ref15658" refString="Olah, J. &amp; Johanson, K. A. (2011) New Neotropical Hydroptilidae (Trichoptera). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 103, 117 - 255." title="New Neotropical Hydroptilidae (Trichoptera)" type="journal article" year="2011">Oláh &amp; Johanson 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Thomson &amp; Holzenthal 2012" authorityName="Thomson &amp; Holzenthal" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="digitata">
<emphasis box="[1316,1333,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1349,1436,1474,1500]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">digitata</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Thomson, R. E. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W." box="[151,488,1510,1536]" firstAuthor="Thomson" journalOrPublisher="ZooKeys" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="19 - 39" part="185" refId="ref15879" refString="Thomson, R. E. &amp; Holzenthal, R. W. (2012) New species and records of Hydroptilidae (Trichoptera) from Venezuela. ZooKeys, 185, 19 - 39. https: // doi. org / 10.3897 / zookeys. 185.2909" title="New species and records of Hydroptilidae (Trichoptera) from Venezuela" type="journal article" year="2012">Thomson &amp; Holzenthal 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Olah &amp; Flint 2012" authorityName="Olah &amp; Flint" authorityYear="2012" box="[501,842,1510,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuskera">
<emphasis box="[501,518,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[534,616,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">tuskera</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Olah, J. &amp; Flint, O. S. Jr." box="[625,842,1510,1536]" firstAuthor="Olah" journalOrPublisher="Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="131 - 213" part="104" refId="ref15616" refString="Olah, J. &amp; Flint, O. S. Jr. (2012) Description of new species in the Leucotrichiini tribe (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae). Annales Historico-Naturales Musei Nationalis Hungarici, 104, 131 - 213." title="Description of new species in the Leucotrichiini tribe (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae)" type="journal article" year="2012">Oláh &amp; Flint 2012</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
), they are placed into the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[1142,1291,1510,1536]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipenis">
<emphasis box="[1142,1159,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1175,1291,1510,1536]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">brevipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group. This group is characterized by having the following features: (1) a costal bulla is usually absent from each forewing (present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[275,421,1582,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipenis">
<emphasis box="[275,292,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[305,421,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">brevipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Olah &amp; Flint" authorityYear="2012" box="[474,586,1582,1608]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tuskera">
<emphasis box="[474,491,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[504,586,1582,1608]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">tuskera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); (2) abdominal segment VII has one long and somewhat capitate ventromesal process, usually with a rugose apex; (3) segment VIII has a pair of conspicuous ventrolateral processes; (4) the inferior appendages are fused to each other, usually with a pair of digitate apicolateral processes.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,1402,1896]" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">
In the phylogenetic analysis presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M." box="[663,883,1690,1717]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Santos" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="458 - 480" part="41" refId="ref15814" refString="Santos, A. P. M., Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M. (2016) Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data. Systematic Entomology, 41, 458 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12168" title="Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data" type="journal article" year="2016">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[744,793,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">et al</emphasis>
. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, species in the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[1048,1194,1690,1716]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipenis">
<emphasis box="[1048,1065,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1078,1194,1690,1716]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">brevipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group did not cluster with those of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mosely" authorityYear="1939" box="[346,497,1726,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="plaumanni">
<emphasis box="[346,363,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[377,497,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">plaumanni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group. However, the placement of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[940,1087,1726,1752]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipenis">
<emphasis box="[940,957,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[971,1087,1726,1752]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">brevipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group remained unclear, since the analyses had no resolution at this point (
<bibRefCitation author="Santos, A. P. M. &amp; Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M." box="[638,843,1762,1789]" etAl="et al." firstAuthor="Santos" journalOrPublisher="Systematic Entomology" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" pagination="458 - 480" part="41" refId="ref15814" refString="Santos, A. P. M., Nessimian, J. L. &amp; Takiya, D. M. (2016) Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data. Systematic Entomology, 41, 458 - 480. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / syen. 12168" title="Revised classification and evolution of leucotrichiine microcaddisflies (Trichoptera: Hydroptilidae) based on morphological and molecular data" type="journal article" year="2016">
Santos 
<emphasis box="[720,769,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). It is likely that the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Flint" authorityYear="1974" box="[1069,1215,1762,1788]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" genus="Acostatrichia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevipenis">
<emphasis box="[1069,1086,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1099,1215,1762,1788]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="210">brevipenis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Group will become a new genus or that its species will be transferred, but with the currently limited knowledge of 
<taxonomicName box="[1222,1398,1798,1824]" class="Insecta" family="Hydroptilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="210" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Leucotrichiinae">Leucotrichiinae</taxonomicName>
diversity and phylogeny, I prefer to clarify the morphological and taxonomic aspects before proposing a new genus name.
</paragraph>
